Bitcoin
The number of transactions in the Bitcoin network has reached the maximum level for the last year. And fees for money transfers in BTC have fallen to a 4-year minimum.
According to the research company Diar , in January 2019 the number of transactions in the bitcoin network reached a maximum in the last year.
At the same time, the median cost of a transaction in US dollars has broken a new anti-record, dropping to the lowest level in the last 5 years.
Transaction fees have also collapsed, Diar claims. In January, the average commission fell to the level of 2015 and amounted to less than $0.1.
